# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# houndmasker .gitignore
#
# This tool handles sensitive data. The rules below exist primarily to make it
# hard to ACCIDENTALLY commit a customer's Active Directory data or the mapping
# file that reverses the masking. Review before removing anything.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- The reversal key: NEVER commit this ----------------------------------
# mapping.json links masked tokens back to real identities. Treat it like a
# credential. Ignored wherever it appears.
mapping.json
**/mapping.json

# --- Tool output ----------------------------------------------------------
# Default date-stamped output dir and common custom names.
modified_files_*/
mod/
masked/
*_masked/
client_masked/
out/
output/

# --- Raw BloodHound / SharpHound collections ------------------------------
# SharpHound CE emits these per-type files (often with a timestamp prefix) and
# a zip. These ARE the sensitive input — keep them out of the repo entirely.
*_domains.json
*_users.json
*_groups.json
*_computers.json
*_gpos.json
*_ous.json
*_containers.json
*_certtemplates.json
*_enterprisecas.json
*_aiacas.json
*_rootcas.json
*_ntauthstores.json
*_issuancepolicies.json
*BloodHound*.zip
*bloodhound*.zip
*.bin

# Local lab / sample data folders
LabFiles/
BHLabFiles/
labdata/
samples/

# --- Internal (not for the public repo) -----------------------------------
# CLAUDE.md is the project knowledge file for our own dev workflow, not for
# users landing on the repo. Keep it local.
CLAUDE.md

# --- Python ---------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
.venv/
venv/
env/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# --- Editors / OS ---------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Env / secrets --------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
